tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I lost a portion of my 20 year old cavity filled molar tooth while eating dinner and wanted to get it addressed at the earliest. Honestly I was looking for a dentist close to my home so that I could make multiple visits easily, if required. A quick Google map search, and I figured that not only is Dr. Rupali's clinic closest to my home, its even the one with the highest rated reviews.

Dr. Rupali is very warm and approachable. She listened to my case and inspected my tooth. Next she brings up a piece of paper and illustrates my tooth, the issue and the options to fix it. She tells me the two options, the pros and cons and which is cost effective. 

Dr. Rupali is methodical in her approach and ensures that he team adheres to her instructions. Before starting the procedure, she tells me in case I feel pain or discomfort to alert her and she will administer anaesthesia. However throughout the procedure I did not feel any pain and the whole procedure completed without any discomfort. Dr. Rupali is very patient and ensured the reconstruction was done perfectly. My session lasted for half an hour and I felt like I got my natural tooth back.

One point worth mentioning is that I had been to the clinic with my seven year old daughter. Dr Rupali made sure my daughter sat in the doctor's cabin during my procedure rather than the waiting lobby. This goes to show her compassion and presence of mind. I'm really thankful to Dr. Rupali's service and would not hesitate to recommend her to anyone requiring an experienced dentist for effective treatment. Thank you Dr. Rupali!
reply_text:
Thanks so much Alston for your kind review.Really appreciate it .Thanks for being such a wonderful patient.Your kind words are motivation for me and my team to serve you and all our patients in more better ways.Be safe.Take care.
Regards Dr Rupali.

review: Found Dr Rupali's clinic reference from practice. Wanted to do dental checkup for my 7 year old son for tooth infection. I choose to go to this clinic first time by looking at reviews. It was really a good service. Dr Rupali explained the issue clearly and suggested RCT. She made my son comfortable before starting process. RCT treatment is generally painful but my son made through it thanks to doctor. Thank you so much.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
I was pleasantly surprised the second I walked in the door...
no pretentious dentists or receptionists here! From the waiting room to the chair, I felt completely at ease, with Dr Rupali checking in on me throughout the entire procedure to ensure I was comfortable and understood what she was doing - and why. 

Dr. Rupali is very calm and gentle, her manner is very soothing and reassuring. With a fantastic experience, I left the clinic feeling confident I'd made the right choice, based purely on my spouse recommendation. 
I am very happy to receive 10 years of warranty on my dental crown.I highly recommend this practice to patients young and old who like to be informed of the treatments they're receiving and being treated like a person, not a number. 

Don‚Äôt bother looking any further!! Five stars *****

review: I had huge gaps between my upper teeth and it was protuding  in the front. I visited dr.rupali's clinic before 3 years to check if braces could be the solution for my problem. She suggested me to go for it and I had my braces.My treatment is done now and I can smile widely with confidence.My spacing and protruding problems are all corrected. Lot of effort has been put by her since mine was a challenging one. Dr.rupali is very professional in her work and so are the visiting orthodontist and surgeon to her clinic.Dr.rupali has a well equipped clinic and the monthly appointments were usually communicated well in advance.Iam very happy with the treatment and outcome.I would totally recommend Dr.rupali's dental clinic for all dental related problems and confident smile.
